Catch-ALL Route Segments 

To handle Route with varying numbers of segments,Next.js provides catch-all segments 

What is it ?

A catch-all segment captures all subsequent path segments into a single array parameter.

if folder structure is  

app
    docs/
        [...slug]/
                page.tsx


matching urls 

/docs -> params.slug []

/docs/getting-started -> params.slug =  ['getting-started]

/docs/getting-started/installation -> params.slug = ['getting-started' ,'installation'] ; 


Use Cases  

1. Documentation pages with hierarchical structures
2. Blog categories and subcategories 
3. Product categories with mutliple levels


Optional Catch all Segments [[...slug]]

To include the base route in the matching ,Next.js offers optional catch-all Segments

What is it ? 

An Optional catch-all segment captures all subsequent path segments into an  array parameter, including the case when no segments are present .



docs -> params.slug = undefined

/docs/getting-started -> params.slug =  ['getting-started]

/docs/getting-started/installation -> params.slug = ['getting-started' ,'installation'] ; 


Feature              Dynamic nested Routes   Catch all    Optional Catch-All 

 Fixed Depth            Yes                    No              No

    Variable Depth      No                     Yes            Yes 

 Matches base Route     No                     No              Yes